<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
        <intro>
            <p>
                Solve the following integrals. 
            </p>
            <!--<p>
                (If an open circle appears on an point which is not a jump discontinuity, ignore it.)
            </p>-->
        </intro>

        <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int_{ {{a1}} }^{ {{b1}} } {{fx}}dx</m>.


                </p>


            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                    <me>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int_{ {{a1}} }^{ {{b1}} } {{fx}}dx = {{Int1}}.</me>
                </p>


            </outtro>
        </knowl>

        <knowl>
            <content>
                <p>
                    <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int {{gx}}dx</m>.


                </p>


            </content>
            <outtro>
                <p>
                    By letting <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} u={{U}}</m>, we have that <m>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} dx = {{dx}}du</m>.  Then by applying parts to the <m>u</m> integral we obtain:
                    <me>\renewcommand{\log}{\ln} \displaystyle \int {{gx}}dx = {{Int2}}+C.</me>
                </p>


            </outtro>
        </knowl>
    
    
        
    
    
    
    
    
   
    
   
